snippet.title: Lesson14 - Refactoring Patterns: Migration vs. Adaptation
snippet.description: In this lesson Mark Richards talks about and demonstrates two patterns for refactoring components and systems: the migration refactoring pattern and the adaptation refactoring pattern. These refactoring patterns can be used for application architecture as well as enterprise architecture. Stay tuned each Monday for more lessons in Software Architecture at https://www.developertoarchitect.com/lessons/.
